data.enText: the smallest unit, consisting of a group of atoms, into which a substance can be divided without a change in its chemical nature

data.chText: 水分子由两个氢原子和一个氧原子构成。
data.enText: A molecule of water consists of two atoms of hydrogen and one atom of oxygen.

simple_means.memory_skill: mole〔= mol〕堆 + cule 小 → 很小的东西堆在一起 → 分子

tr: (nontechnical usage) a tiny piece of anything
(physics and chemistry) the simplest structural unit of an element or compound

value.def: A molecule is the smallest amount of a chemical substance which can exist by itself.

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft supp N
